text: we actually fled the Keys on Tuesday
night because we had a doctor's
appointment on Wednesday morning to
check on the status of the baby which
was my due date September 6 and about an
hour after leaving the doctor I started
to go into labor so the next morning we
found ourselves at the hospital in labor
and they admitted us and that night we
had our baby girl at 10:47 p.m. when
when they finally did discharge us was
starting to get you know windy and we're
getting some gusts of rain and wind and
and the sheriff's were outside the
building and they offered to escort us
to the hotel and we don't know the
condition of our house we don't have any
way of getting down there to find out
the condition of our house marathon is
pretty much under water still and that
was about 30 miles from our house so we
don't really know the status of the
place where we live and right now
they're not letting anybody into the
keys and we don't really have any
substantial information about when we
might be able to get back I also have a
business down there so you know we we
have both our our home and our business
and pretty much our whole life is down
